# SmartHaus M365 AI Workforce AI Agent Governance Rules

## Status

Review document to check yourself

## Quick Start

```bash
make ai-status || true
make ai-health-check || true
make ai-validate
```

## Validate (one command)

```bash
make ai-validate
```

Runs quality gate (lint + tests + docs) plus contract and traceability gates.

## Quality Gates

```bash
make quality-gate
make test-all
make lint-all
make contract-gate
make traceability-gate
```

## SmartHaus M365 AI Workforce Services

| Service | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| user-service | User profiles, authentication, roles |
| request-service | Task request creation and management |
| messaging-service | Job-scoped messaging between users |
| notification-service | Push notifications (acceptance, messaging) |
| moderation-service | Block/report functionality, contractor detection |
| api-gateway | Main API entry point and routing |

## Required Reading

**MANDATORY:** Before any work, read:

1. `Operations/NORTHSTAR.md` - Vision and goals (source of truth - everything must align)
2. `Operations/EXECUTION_PLAN.md` - Planned work (verify work is in plan)
3. `.cursor/rules/agent-workflow-mandatory.mdc` - Unified workflow (MANDATORY)
4. `Operations/EXECUTION_PLAN.md` - Current project state
5. `AGENTS.md` - Agent specifications
6. `contracts/traceability_manifest.yml` - Traceability enforcement

## Mandatory Validation Rules

- NEVER assume previous work is done; ALWAYS validate
- ALWAYS run tests; failing tests = not done
- VERIFY dependencies and functionality; docs ≠ working code
- If you can't run it, it doesn't work

## Forbidden Actions

- Skipping validation or trusting claims
- "Good enough" code, skipped tests, known bugs, partial features
- Vague commits without rationale/decisions
- Modifying contracts without updating dependent services
- Implementing v2+ features in v1 (see Authorized Capabilities in NORTHSTAR.md)
